1. e4 e6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. e5 Nfd7 5. d4 c5 6. dxc5 Nc6 7. Bf4 Nxc5 {Our pet move.} 8. Qd2 {It looks like White might be planning to castle queenside, so Black prepares a pawn rush there.} 8... a6 9. O-O-O {And so it begins!} 9... b5 $1 {With this move, Black gains a good deal of space on the queenside and prepares the ...b4 idea.} 10. Kb1 b4 $1 {Forcing White's Knight away from the defense of the e4 square ...} 11. Ne2 Ne4 $1 {... so that a Black Knight can settle there.} 12. Qe3 Bc5 $1 {
A standard idea: Black tries to pull White's Knight away from e2.} 13. Nfd4 {White is stubborn and keeps that Knight on e2, but Black builds up more pressure on the pinned Knight at d4.} (13. Ned4 Qb6 {sets up a threat of 14... Nc3+, since White does not have a Knight on e2 to cover the c3 square.}) 13... Qb6 14. Ka1 Na5 {Shifting position. Black decides that this Knight will be stronger at c4, where it hits e3 and b2.} 15. f3 Nc4 {As advertised. White's King is already looking terribly beleaguered.} 16. Qg1 Nc3 $1 {This sacrifice is completely sound. Black has an overwhelming amount of material around White's King.} 17. bxc3 Na3 (17... bxc3 {looks very strong, but White can respond with} 18. Rb1 {when it is not clear how the attack should be continued.}) 18. Qe3 (18. c4 {buys White a little time, but Black's attack remains terribly strong. Here is a possible variation, just to illustrate Black's ideas in this position.} 18... dxc4 19. Rc1 Bb7 20. Be3 Rc8 21. Kb2 O-O 22. Qf2 c3+ 23. Ka1 Nc4 24. Bg5 Bd5 25. Qh4 Qa5 26. Nb3 Qa3 27. Rb1 Nd2 $1 28. Qe1 Bxb3 29. cxb3 Rfd8 30. Bxd8 Nxb1 31. Qxb1 Rxd8 $19 {and Black mates in a few more moves, with threats including ...Rd2, ...Rd1, and ...Bd4.}) 18... Nxc2+ $1 {Black picks up the Queen for two minor pieces. Since she sacrificed one piece going in, that is a net of three pieces for the Queen. But Black also has extra pawns, and the White King is terribly exposed.} 19. Nxc2 Bxe3 20. Bxe3 Qc7 21. Bd4 a5 22. Ne3 Ba6 23. Nf4
O-O 24. Rc1 b3 25. axb3 Rfb8 26. Rb1 Bc4 27. Bxc4 dxc4 28. bxc4 Qc6 29. Rb5 Rxb5 30. cxb5 Qxb5 31. Rb1 Qa4+ 32. Kb2 Rb8+ 33. Kc1 Qa3+ {White is going to lose a Rook.} (33... Qa3+ 34. Kc2 Qa2+ 35. Kd3 Qxb1+ {etc.}) 0-1

