1. e4 Nf6 {What?! This is Alekhine's Defense. But the way White plays it, we transpose pretty quickly into a French.} 2. Nc3 d5 3. e5 Nfd7 4. d4 c5 5. dxc5 e6 6. Nf3 {Back to normal!} 6... Nc6 7. Bf4 Nxc5 8. Bb5 {This pin is unusual and not very good. Black is happy if White wants to exchange off his good Bishop.} 8... a6 9. Bxc6+ bxc6 10. O-O Be7 11. Nd4 Qc7 12. Qg4 g5 $5 {Sharp, strange tactics!} 13. Be3 (13. Bxg5 Rg8 14. f4 h6 {wins material for Black.}) 13... Nd7 14. Qh5 Nxe5 {The point: Black picks up White's last center pawn.} 15. Bxg5 Ng6 16. Bxe7 Nxe7 17. Rfe1 Ng6 18. g3 O-O 19. f4 Qb6 20. Nce2 c5 21. Nf3 Qxb2 22. c3 f6 23. g4 Ra7 24. f5 exf5 25. gxf5 Ne5 26. Nxe5 fxe5 27. f6 Rxf6 28. Qe8+ Rf8 29. Qxe5 Rg7+ 30. Ng3 Qf2+ 31. Kh1 Bb7 $1 {Oops! A deadly discovered check comes next.}
0-1

